sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  Client      ->> ShinyServer: request Shiny map app with a cell-values layer
  ShinyServer ->> DuckDB:      cell_stats(sql) for legend min/max
  DuckDB      ->> ShinyServer: {n, min, max, mean, std, p2, p50, p98}
  ShinyServer ->> Client:      return JS with tile URL template incl. base64(SQL) + colormap + rescale + mtime
  loop for every tile in the current viewport (z/x/y)
    Client      ->> Varnish:      request /msens/tiles/{z}/{x}/{y}.png?sql=...&colormap=...&rescale=...
    alt cache hit
      Varnish   ->> Client:       return cached PNG (< 1 ms)
    else cache miss
      Varnish   ->> TiTiler:      pass request through
      Note over TiTiler: validate SQL (sqlglot), LRU-cache the per-SQL cell_id→value map
      TiTiler   ->> DuckDB:        execute SELECT cell_id, value FROM ...
      DuckDB    ->> TiTiler:       rows (once per unique SQL, then LRU-cached)
      TiTiler   ->> CellIdCOG:     read z/x/y window (nearest-neighbor) from r_cellid.tif
      CellIdCOG ->> TiTiler:       (1, 256, 256) uint32 cell-id tile
      Note over TiTiler: lookup value per cell_id, rescale + colormap, render PNG
      TiTiler   ->> Varnish:       PNG (cached 7 d)
      Varnish   ->> Client:        return PNG
    end
  end
